Ted Odogwu, Kano. The  Kano State Road and Traffic Agency on Thursday impounded  a truckload  of  fake and substandard drugs worth  N7m being smuggled into the state. Spokesman for KAROTA, Nabulisi  Na’isa,  said  in a statement that they had handed the  truck and  the  contraband  to the state task force on drugs. He said, “The Managing Director of the agency, Baffa  Agundi, has directed that the vehicle and its entire content  to be handed over immediately to the state task force on drug abuse constituted by Governor Abdullahi Ganduje for further investigation.” Our correspondent learnt that    when the owner of the prohibited items sighted KAROTA officials, who were attempting to arrest him, he fled, abandoning  the truck. Na’isa  urged the public to continue to support and encourage the agency. Copyright PUNCH.
